  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2908",
  "title": "fix(index.es6): avoid use of Object.assign for IE",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nIn a recent PR (https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/2885) we updated all references to `Object.assign` for IE. But we forgot to update the entry point of the `es` build. The lib breaks in IE when the it's bundled with Webpack & friends.\r\n\r\nWe don't need to use the spread operator because with the previous `Object.assign` call we already mutate the factory. So we can directly assign the two attributes on it.",
